The paper proposes a method for hyper-parameter optimization to learn features that generalize across tasks and domains. This is a common problem in machine learning, which is typically addressed in the sub-fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper focuses on few-shot image classification, which is a specific task within computer vision, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques, which are also commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
